1
00:00:45,178 --> 00:00:48,982
Sometimes, one minute
can change everything.

2
00:01:43,069 --> 00:01:44,304
Nice to meet you.

3
00:01:45,972 --> 00:01:47,240
I'm Do Min-ik.

4
00:01:55,482 --> 00:01:57,617
Nice to meet you. I'm Do Min-ik.

5
00:02:00,687 --> 00:02:01,921
Nice to meet you.

6
00:02:03,556 --> 00:02:04,691
My name is Eun Jeong-su.

7
00:02:09,662 --> 00:02:10,830
This guy.

8
00:02:11,698 --> 00:02:12,832
It's him, right?

9
00:02:20,874 --> 00:02:22,075
Did you meet him?

10
00:02:22,342 --> 00:02:24,677
Yes, I met him just now.

11
00:02:25,178 --> 00:02:26,746
How did it go?

12
00:02:28,882 --> 00:02:29,983
Mr. Gi!

13
00:02:36,422 --> 00:02:39,025
Let's talk later.

14
00:02:45,031 --> 00:02:46,065
Who is he?

15
00:02:47,600 --> 00:02:49,636
He's Min-ik's new driver.

16
00:02:50,537 --> 00:02:52,772
Are you free sometime this week?

17
00:02:53,039 --> 00:02:54,507
I'd like to make some plans.

18
00:02:56,576 --> 00:02:57,944
It's about the thing I said earlier.

19
00:03:13,426 --> 00:03:14,627
No way.

20
00:03:15,795 --> 00:03:17,130
It can't be.

21
00:03:17,530 --> 00:03:19,165
It's impossible.

22
00:03:19,232 --> 00:03:20,366
Ha-ni.

23
00:03:20,667 --> 00:03:22,402
-What are you doing?
-Myeong-jeong.

24
00:03:24,971 --> 00:03:27,907
Guys, gather around.

25
00:03:28,942 --> 00:03:31,611
This is what happened
on my way to work this morning.

26
00:03:31,911 --> 00:03:34,914
I swear I saw something red flash by
in front of me.

27
00:03:36,849 --> 00:03:39,219
Are you saying you saw Jeong Gal-hee?

28
00:03:39,686 --> 00:03:43,189
She'd never come back here
unless she has no brains.

29
00:03:43,289 --> 00:03:45,291
Swallows come back in the spring,

30
00:03:45,358 --> 00:03:47,694
and beggars always come back
knocking on your door,

31
00:03:47,760 --> 00:03:49,362
but Gal-hee never will.

32
00:03:49,562 --> 00:03:52,365
How could she work for someone
whom she tried to kill?

33
00:04:00,673 --> 00:04:02,976
Here's my schedule for this week.

34
00:04:03,209 --> 00:04:07,280
And this is the joint meeting schedule.
My number's changed.

35
00:04:07,914 --> 00:04:10,149
-Save it.
-Yes, sir.

36
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:12,752
About lunch, do you know that place,
Lepommi, in Cheongdam-dong?

37
00:04:12,819 --> 00:04:14,621
Get some truffle gnocchi for me there.

38
00:04:15,355 --> 00:04:17,724
Also, stop by Yeonnam-dong
on your way back and...

39
00:04:21,828 --> 00:04:22,929
get...

40
00:04:34,040 --> 00:04:35,308
Bend down, will you?

41
00:04:35,608 --> 00:04:36,709
I can't.

42
00:04:37,443 --> 00:04:39,879
-Why not?
-"Tell me what you want."

43
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:42,248
You said that, didn't you?

44
00:04:42,782 --> 00:04:43,716
Did I?

45
00:04:43,783 --> 00:04:46,185
"I'll revise the contract as you wish."

46
00:04:46,252 --> 00:04:47,553
You said that too.

47
00:04:48,221 --> 00:04:50,223
-Did I say that?
-Also,

48
00:04:50,290 --> 00:04:53,159
even after I turned you down,
you showed up again and said,

49
00:04:53,893 --> 00:04:56,529
"I can only see you."

50
00:04:56,796 --> 00:04:58,231
You sounded extremely desperate.

51
00:04:58,298 --> 00:05:00,033
No, I didn't.

52
00:05:01,067 --> 00:05:04,137
"Gal-hee, I can only--"

53
00:05:04,203 --> 00:05:05,571
That's enough!

54
00:05:06,673 --> 00:05:09,275
Fine, tell me what you want.

55
00:05:11,444 --> 00:05:13,313
CONDITIONS FOR CONTRACT RENEWAL

56
00:05:14,080 --> 00:05:15,915
"Working hours are from 9 a.m.

57
00:05:16,282 --> 00:05:18,751
to 8 p.m.

58
00:05:19,252 --> 00:05:22,422
I refuse to take calls
outside working hours

59
00:05:22,622 --> 00:05:24,791
or run personal errands

60
00:05:24,857 --> 00:05:26,526
unrelated to work.

61
00:05:27,060 --> 00:05:29,762
I demand an hour of lunch break every day.

62
00:05:29,829 --> 00:05:32,899
I work five days a week
unless decided otherwise."

63
00:05:34,767 --> 00:05:38,971
Since when do secretaries have
set working hours?

64
00:05:39,706 --> 00:05:42,108
As a secretary,
you go home when your boss does.

65
00:05:42,342 --> 00:05:46,012
You work whenever your boss is working.

66
00:05:46,412 --> 00:05:50,350
I'm back here
as a secretary of T&T Mobile,

67
00:05:51,084 --> 00:05:54,387
not Do Min-ik's minion.

68
00:05:56,756 --> 00:05:59,425
If you don't work on weekends,
who will feed my fish?

69
00:05:59,492 --> 00:06:01,394
That's animal abuse.

70
00:06:01,461 --> 00:06:03,129
Are you aware

71
00:06:03,196 --> 00:06:06,599
I've been skipping meals
to feed your fish every weekend?

72
00:06:06,733 --> 00:06:08,701
That's abuse.

73
00:06:08,768 --> 00:06:11,704
Are you saying you don't care
if my fish starves?

74
00:06:13,239 --> 00:06:15,975
"Anyone could do what you do.

75
00:06:16,743 --> 00:06:18,544
It doesn't have to be you."

76
00:06:18,745 --> 00:06:20,346
You said that yourself,

77
00:06:20,413 --> 00:06:21,681
didn't you?

78
00:06:22,315 --> 00:06:23,449
That means

79
00:06:24,117 --> 00:06:27,620
anyone could do it.

80
00:06:33,326 --> 00:06:34,694
Well,

81
00:06:35,294 --> 00:06:37,630
if you'd rather I left,

82
00:06:38,398 --> 00:06:42,001
I will do so willingly.

83
00:06:51,077 --> 00:06:53,079
Fine, all right.

84
00:06:53,613 --> 00:06:55,114
But there's one condition.

85
00:06:55,181 --> 00:06:56,282
Fire away.

86
00:06:56,482 --> 00:06:59,385
Your boss isn't the kind of person

87
00:06:59,919 --> 00:07:01,087
who gives up easily.

88
00:07:01,154 --> 00:07:02,955
I have an illness, so what?

89
00:07:03,022 --> 00:07:05,124
Even if my illness can't be cured,

90
00:07:05,558 --> 00:07:07,827
I won't let it drag me down.
I'll push through it.

91
00:07:07,894 --> 00:07:10,163
I'll win the approval of the board
and become

92
00:07:10,229 --> 00:07:11,431
the CEO of T&T Mobile.

93
00:07:11,497 --> 00:07:13,766
"From TV to mobile,
from movies to mobile."

94
00:07:13,833 --> 00:07:16,035
I will realize the dream
of running a contents business

95
00:07:16,669 --> 00:07:18,571
that my father never got to realize.

96
00:07:18,971 --> 00:07:20,807
so do everything you can to help me.

97
00:07:20,873 --> 00:07:24,310
No one can find out about my illness.

98
00:07:24,444 --> 00:07:26,746
People should think
that I see every fine line

99
00:07:26,913 --> 00:07:30,283
and every little pore and hair
on their faces.

100
00:07:30,349 --> 00:07:31,417
Got it?

101
00:07:32,785 --> 00:07:34,320
Yes, Mr. Do.

102
00:07:34,620 --> 00:07:36,389
-Is that the only condition?
-No.

103
00:07:37,457 --> 00:07:38,624
There's one more.

104
00:07:51,070 --> 00:07:54,106
And it's a very

105
00:07:54,674 --> 00:07:56,442
important one.

106
00:08:02,248 --> 00:08:03,749
What is it?

107
00:08:06,385 --> 00:08:08,187
As soon as my illness is cured,

108
00:08:08,621 --> 00:08:11,991
the contract between you and me

109
00:08:14,727 --> 00:08:15,895
will be terminated immediately.

110
00:08:28,608 --> 00:08:29,675
Darn it.

111
00:08:30,276 --> 00:08:32,945
All he needed was someone
who could tell people apart for him.

112
00:08:34,580 --> 00:08:38,751
Fine. Whatever. I'll just do
as much as I get paid.

113
00:08:51,531 --> 00:08:52,665
Buses...

114
00:08:55,034 --> 00:08:56,202
are running?

115
00:09:01,007 --> 00:09:02,508
The sun is still up.

116
00:09:05,011 --> 00:09:06,546
There are people on the street.

117
00:09:11,450 --> 00:09:12,852
Are you watching, Mom?

118
00:09:12,919 --> 00:09:16,789
Your daughter finally made it.

119
00:09:21,260 --> 00:09:23,796
I got off work when everyone else did.

120
00:09:26,399 --> 00:09:29,268
This is what I call happiness!

121
00:09:41,881 --> 00:09:43,449
-Jeong Gal-hee?
-Jeong Gal-hee?

122
00:09:54,093 --> 00:09:55,861
I know, I get it.

123
00:09:56,362 --> 00:09:58,731
You all must be puzzled.

124
00:09:58,831 --> 00:10:02,034
Knock, knock, any brains there?

125
00:10:02,802 --> 00:10:04,437
If so, please explain.

126
00:10:04,503 --> 00:10:06,172
How could you go from "I want to kill him"

127
00:10:06,238 --> 00:10:08,174
to "I want to work for him" overnight?

128
00:10:09,775 --> 00:10:11,477
What's the fuss about?

129
00:10:13,112 --> 00:10:15,281
-Hello, Ms. Lee.
-Hello, Ms. Lee.

130
00:10:15,615 --> 00:10:17,216
I asked her to come.

131
00:10:17,316 --> 00:10:18,484
Please.

132
00:10:21,087 --> 00:10:23,589
Ms. Lee, let me explain.

133
00:10:24,090 --> 00:10:26,525
You can work anywhere you want
as long as you're paid.

134
00:10:26,592 --> 00:10:28,361
What's the big deal?

135
00:10:28,761 --> 00:10:30,863
Welcome back. I'm glad to see you again.

136
00:10:31,263 --> 00:10:32,832
Thank you, Ms. Lee.

137
00:10:33,666 --> 00:10:35,468
Today's on me, everyone.

138
00:10:39,905 --> 00:10:42,274
What are they doing near my workplace?

139
00:10:43,309 --> 00:10:44,377
Who?

140
00:10:46,946 --> 00:10:48,681
Ms. Lee, I'm really sorry,

141
00:10:48,748 --> 00:10:50,149
but I have to go.

142
00:10:50,216 --> 00:10:52,351
Where's the bill?

143
00:10:52,418 --> 00:10:54,420
Don't worry. It must be
something urgent. I'll get this.

144
00:10:54,487 --> 00:10:56,355
Thank you so much, Ms. Lee.

145
00:10:56,422 --> 00:10:58,424
Let's drink and sing karaoke soon.
It's my treat.

146
00:10:58,491 --> 00:10:59,659
We'll have a blast.

147
00:10:59,725 --> 00:11:01,360
Can you take us to a club instead?

148
00:11:01,427 --> 00:11:04,130
Sure. I'm sorry. I'm really sorry.

149
00:11:04,196 --> 00:11:05,297
-Keep your promise!
-Okay.

150
00:11:05,364 --> 00:11:06,399
A club...

151
00:11:06,465 --> 00:11:09,035
-Have you ever been to a club?
-No.

152
00:11:12,605 --> 00:11:14,273
Don't you see this?

153
00:11:14,340 --> 00:11:15,841
I don't care if you're police officers.

154
00:11:15,908 --> 00:11:18,077
I still can't let you in.

155
00:11:18,144 --> 00:11:19,945
Sir, we're busy.

156
00:11:20,012 --> 00:11:23,115
This is obstruction of justice.

157
00:11:23,482 --> 00:11:25,751
-Excuse me!
-Ma'am.

158
00:11:26,352 --> 00:11:28,320
-Do you remember us?
-So it really was her.

159
00:11:28,387 --> 00:11:30,056
With Mr. Do Min-ik--

160
00:11:31,657 --> 00:11:32,658
Do Min-ik?

161
00:11:32,892 --> 00:11:34,794
I'm sorry,

162
00:11:35,127 --> 00:11:37,396
but can we talk somewhere else?

163
00:11:37,463 --> 00:11:39,799
Where's Mr. Do now?

164
00:11:41,233 --> 00:11:43,269
-Look.
-Yes, sir.

165
00:11:43,335 --> 00:11:46,105
You're close to that girl
in the red cardigan, aren't you?

166
00:11:46,505 --> 00:11:49,108
Find out what Do Min-ik, that punk,
is up to these days.

167
00:11:49,675 --> 00:11:50,810
I will.

168
00:12:02,054 --> 00:12:03,622
From morning to night,

169
00:12:04,690 --> 00:12:06,425
I'm giving you many presents today.

170
00:12:13,899 --> 00:12:15,634
What's the present
you sent me this morning?

171
00:12:16,235 --> 00:12:17,470
Do you mean Ms. Jeong?

172
00:12:18,471 --> 00:12:20,039
Is Ms. Jeong back?

173
00:12:21,340 --> 00:12:22,508
That's not it?

174
00:12:24,710 --> 00:12:25,978
I spent all my budget for this month

175
00:12:26,045 --> 00:12:28,013
just to break this to you.

176
00:12:28,180 --> 00:12:30,015
But if Ms. Jeong is back,

177
00:12:32,618 --> 00:12:34,754
this really is a perfect time
to celebrate.

178
00:12:38,324 --> 00:12:40,893
What is it you want to tell me?
Why would you spend so much money?

179
00:12:41,494 --> 00:12:42,595
You want to ask me for a favor?

180
00:12:42,962 --> 00:12:44,096
I want to confess something.

181
00:12:45,097 --> 00:12:46,265
Dae-ju?

182
00:12:46,699 --> 00:12:48,934
This was at 11:53 p.m.

183
00:12:49,702 --> 00:12:53,172
It means he was already there
when you arrived.

184
00:12:53,706 --> 00:12:56,909
Then where did he go without seeing you?

185
00:13:01,647 --> 00:13:03,315
I don't want to fight over

186
00:13:03,382 --> 00:13:04,984
who's going to say it first.

187
00:13:05,184 --> 00:13:07,720
So let me say it first.

188
00:13:08,487 --> 00:13:10,256
Ladies first, of course.

189
00:13:13,726 --> 00:13:15,561
I had an accident

190
00:13:16,996 --> 00:13:18,464
the day we were supposed to meet here.

191
00:13:19,231 --> 00:13:20,332
An accident?

192
00:13:21,033 --> 00:13:22,701
I was waiting for you...

193
00:13:41,987 --> 00:13:43,522
I can't tell

194
00:13:45,090 --> 00:13:47,626
if he's genuinely surprised by this

195
00:13:47,993 --> 00:13:49,895
or just pretending to be.

196
00:13:51,797 --> 00:13:54,934
Still, I believe his face would be saying,

197
00:13:56,302 --> 00:13:59,438
"I'm very worried about you."

198
00:14:06,679 --> 00:14:07,813
THAT PLACE

199
00:14:07,880 --> 00:14:09,114
Has the culprit been caught?

200
00:14:09,882 --> 00:14:11,116
Did you see his face?

201
00:14:11,350 --> 00:14:13,085
I did,

202
00:14:14,186 --> 00:14:15,454
but he's not caught yet.

203
00:14:18,090 --> 00:14:19,525
I hope you didn't get hurt.

204
00:14:20,626 --> 00:14:22,394
I did get hurt a little.

205
00:14:23,896 --> 00:14:25,030
Hold on.

206
00:14:33,939 --> 00:14:35,841
-Who are you?
-Well...

207
00:14:36,642 --> 00:14:38,744
I didn't know you were both here.

208
00:14:39,612 --> 00:14:42,815
You don't need that dangerous thing.
We're police officers.

209
00:14:52,858 --> 00:14:54,026
Ms. Jeong?

210
00:15:04,837 --> 00:15:07,873
Is this why you're suspecting me?

211
00:15:07,940 --> 00:15:11,577
When you want to kill someone,
it's usually someone you know,

212
00:15:12,111 --> 00:15:13,812
and most likely someone close to you.

213
00:15:14,680 --> 00:15:18,183
Seventy-five percent of murderers
are the victim's acquaintances.

214
00:15:18,617 --> 00:15:19,785
Sir.

215
00:15:22,755 --> 00:15:24,857
If there's any doubt,
it should be cleared up.

216
00:15:24,924 --> 00:15:26,325
Here's what happened.

217
00:15:30,729 --> 00:15:32,197
I went to the boat to meet Min-ik.

218
00:15:33,532 --> 00:15:34,767
Hello, Ms. Lee.

219
00:15:35,768 --> 00:15:36,936
Ms. Lee?

220
00:15:37,369 --> 00:15:40,272
But something happened
to my secretary, Ms. Lee.

221
00:15:40,439 --> 00:15:41,340
Ms. Lee.

222
00:15:41,407 --> 00:15:42,608
So I left.

223
00:15:44,543 --> 00:15:46,912
Min-ik wouldn't answer his phone,

224
00:15:48,013 --> 00:15:50,149
so I got worried

225
00:15:50,849 --> 00:15:52,785
and went back to the boat afterward.

226
00:15:55,587 --> 00:15:56,722
Excuse me.

227
00:16:01,694 --> 00:16:02,795
Well...

228
00:16:03,395 --> 00:16:05,364
Can I borrow your phone?

229
00:16:05,431 --> 00:16:08,100
I need to make an urgent phone call,
but my phone is dead.

230
00:16:11,637 --> 00:16:12,705
Thank you.

231
00:16:18,010 --> 00:16:20,045
If I'd known he was the culprit,

232
00:16:22,047 --> 00:16:23,782
I would've taken a closer look.

233
00:16:26,352 --> 00:16:28,454
Did you pay with a credit card
in the taxi?

234
00:16:28,821 --> 00:16:31,290
-I paid with cash.
-"Cash"?

235
00:16:31,623 --> 00:16:35,260
Who pays with cash in a taxi these days?

236
00:16:35,561 --> 00:16:37,696
That's why I try to pay with cash.

237
00:16:38,063 --> 00:16:41,400
Taxi drivers love it
when they hold cash in their hand.

238
00:16:42,234 --> 00:16:44,069
That's nice of you.

239
00:16:46,405 --> 00:16:49,274
Write down your secretary's phone number
for me.

240
00:16:49,942 --> 00:16:52,111
Do you have to talk to her?

241
00:16:52,311 --> 00:16:53,445
If I don't,

242
00:16:53,812 --> 00:16:56,181
how will you prove your alibi?

243
00:17:04,490 --> 00:17:06,191
You don't have to.

244
00:17:06,692 --> 00:17:08,694
I want the investigation terminated.

245
00:17:09,094 --> 00:17:10,229
Mr. Do.

246
00:17:10,629 --> 00:17:12,865
Are you kidding me?

247
00:17:13,665 --> 00:17:17,002
One moment you nag us to find the culprit,

248
00:17:17,703 --> 00:17:19,938
the next you want
the investigation terminated.

249
00:17:20,539 --> 00:17:24,109
Do you think you can boss around
the police?

250
00:17:24,276 --> 00:17:26,545
Am I one of your secretaries?

251
00:17:27,246 --> 00:17:28,947
I want the investigation terminated
as well.

252
00:17:30,716 --> 00:17:32,051
-Pardon?
-The CEO election is

253
00:17:32,117 --> 00:17:33,252
around the corner.

254
00:17:33,352 --> 00:17:35,888
Everyone's dying to spread rumors.
The police, a murder attempt...

255
00:17:36,188 --> 00:17:37,723
It'd make people go crazy.

256
00:17:38,057 --> 00:17:40,626
Imagine reporters smelling something
and joining in too.

257
00:17:41,226 --> 00:17:42,961
It'll put Min-ik in serious trouble.

258
00:17:43,996 --> 00:17:47,299
Considering nothing more has happened
since then, I wouldn't worry.

259
00:17:47,766 --> 00:17:49,802
You said 75 percent.

260
00:17:50,602 --> 00:17:52,805
Then there's the other 25 percent too.

261
00:17:55,207 --> 00:17:57,042
Can you believe these guys?

262
00:18:00,546 --> 00:18:02,014
You can't be too careful.

263
00:18:02,081 --> 00:18:04,650
Always take your car
even to personal appointments.

264
00:18:04,817 --> 00:18:07,386
Sir, I hope you understand.

265
00:18:07,586 --> 00:18:09,288
Sure, don't worry.

266
00:18:09,388 --> 00:18:10,956
Or how about this?

267
00:18:11,356 --> 00:18:13,358
Get a bodyguard.

268
00:18:13,592 --> 00:18:14,993
