00:37:08,759 --> 00:37:10,761
Can I ask her first and call you back?

545
00:37:10,895 --> 00:37:12,997
Then please ask her if she could meet him

546
00:37:13,064 --> 00:37:15,566
at the Kingdom Hotel
at 9 p.m. on the 13th.

547
00:37:15,766 --> 00:37:17,301
KINGDOM HOTEL AT 9 P. M. ON THE 13TH

548
00:37:18,469 --> 00:37:19,570
Please wait.

549
00:37:19,837 --> 00:37:20,905
Hello, Ms. Park.

550
00:37:20,972 --> 00:37:22,640
I just got a call from T&T Mobile.

551
00:37:22,707 --> 00:37:25,243
I know. At 9 p.m. on the 13th.

552
00:37:29,814 --> 00:37:31,515
She already knows.

553
00:37:32,350 --> 00:37:33,417
Really?

554
00:37:35,953 --> 00:37:39,557
Then I'll make a reservation
under the name of T&T Mobile.

555
00:37:40,524 --> 00:37:41,592
Bye.

556
00:37:43,894 --> 00:37:45,062
How did she know?

557
00:37:46,130 --> 00:37:48,866
Did Chairwoman Sim tell her directly?

558
00:37:50,901 --> 00:37:52,370
Is this fate?

559
00:37:54,272 --> 00:37:55,940
Fate?

560
00:37:56,440 --> 00:37:58,576
Am I talking to a doctor
or a fortune-teller?

561
00:37:59,176 --> 00:38:01,112
When is Dr. Park coming back from the US?

562
00:38:01,345 --> 00:38:04,649
What you're saying
can't be explained by medicine.

563
00:38:04,715 --> 00:38:06,717
You can only see
one person's face clearly?

564
00:38:06,817 --> 00:38:08,019
I mean...

565
00:38:08,753 --> 00:38:10,955
Does that really make no sense?

566
00:38:11,022 --> 00:38:12,623
It doesn't.

567
00:38:13,324 --> 00:38:15,159
With the damaged area in your brain,

568
00:38:15,226 --> 00:38:16,861
you should not recognize any faces at all.

569
00:38:16,927 --> 00:38:19,630
It doesn't make sense
to recognize a certain face.

570
00:38:19,830 --> 00:38:21,999
Then what's going on?

571
00:38:22,533 --> 00:38:25,036
-Is she bald?
-No.

572
00:38:25,102 --> 00:38:26,771
-Does she have a big mole?
-No.

573
00:38:26,837 --> 00:38:29,940
Then is it Chanel No. 5?

574
00:38:30,441 --> 00:38:32,677
Does she wear a lot of perfume?

575
00:38:32,743 --> 00:38:35,112
Does she wear the same uniform every day?

576
00:38:38,349 --> 00:38:40,017
She doesn't wear a uniform,

577
00:38:40,584 --> 00:38:42,520
but she does wear
pretty much the same clothes

578
00:38:43,454 --> 00:38:44,889
every day.

579
00:38:45,990 --> 00:38:48,726
There's another possibility.

580
00:38:49,393 --> 00:38:50,394
What is it?

581
00:38:51,028 --> 00:38:52,196
An imprint.

582
00:38:54,165 --> 00:38:55,266
An imprint?

583
00:38:57,168 --> 00:39:00,104
The hairstyle, bags, and clothes
she wears every day

584
00:39:00,171 --> 00:39:02,573
are imprinted in your mind,

585
00:39:02,640 --> 00:39:04,375
and it helps you recognize her.

586
00:39:05,109 --> 00:39:07,311
It's not your eyes that see her face.

587
00:39:07,378 --> 00:39:10,348
It's your brain that's imprinted with her.

588
00:39:10,881 --> 00:39:13,484
"This person wears this perfume."

589
00:39:13,551 --> 00:39:15,486
"This woman always wears a red cardigan."

590
00:39:15,553 --> 00:39:18,055
It's like when thinking of a mustache

591
00:39:18,122 --> 00:39:21,459
makes you remember Charlie Chaplin's face.

592
00:39:36,307 --> 00:39:37,441
Now that I think of it,

593
00:39:38,109 --> 00:39:39,944
whenever she was with me,

594
00:39:40,945 --> 00:39:42,613
she was wearing a red cardigan.

595
00:39:53,624 --> 00:39:55,226
Hello, Mr. Do.

596
00:40:05,803 --> 00:40:08,572
May I ask what you're doing?

597
00:40:14,245 --> 00:40:16,847
Mr. Do, what are you doing?

598
00:40:26,023 --> 00:40:27,124
Ms. Jeong.

599
00:41:00,658 --> 00:41:02,226
-Take off your clothes.
-Pardon?

600
00:41:04,862 --> 00:41:06,497
Mr. Do.

601
00:41:06,897 --> 00:41:09,500
This counts as sexual harassment.

602
00:41:09,567 --> 00:41:10,634
Then

603
00:41:11,068 --> 00:41:12,136
put on more clothes.

604
00:41:14,572 --> 00:41:17,007
Let me see. Put this on.

605
00:41:17,441 --> 00:41:18,742
There you go.

606
00:41:19,910 --> 00:41:21,178
Put this tie on too.

607
00:41:23,013 --> 00:41:24,815
Put it on.

608
00:41:25,382 --> 00:41:26,851
Take off your glasses.

609
00:41:28,052 --> 00:41:29,186
Change shoes too.

610
00:41:31,155 --> 00:41:33,290
Put on these shoes instead.

611
00:41:33,791 --> 00:41:35,025
Can you put your hair down?

612
00:41:35,693 --> 00:41:36,994
I'll give you three minutes.

613
00:41:38,395 --> 00:41:40,464
Tell me when you're done.

614
00:41:51,141 --> 00:41:53,344
Who would've known
being a secretary would be this hard?

615
00:42:03,454 --> 00:42:06,090
I'm done. You can come in.

616
00:42:32,249 --> 00:42:33,284
Ms. Jeong.

617
00:43:16,527 --> 00:43:18,729
What's wrong? Are you not feeling well?

618
00:43:19,263 --> 00:43:21,599
No, I'm not.

619
00:43:23,233 --> 00:43:24,568
I'm not feeling well at all.

620
00:43:25,636 --> 00:43:27,237
Fate, my foot.

621
00:43:27,805 --> 00:43:28,939
Ms. Jeong.

622
00:43:29,206 --> 00:43:31,909
Well... Our contract...

623
00:43:31,976 --> 00:43:33,911
-It's not--
-Oh, our contract?

624
00:43:34,678 --> 00:43:38,148
I thought you might change your mind.

625
00:43:38,916 --> 00:43:41,518
So I just had it notarized.

626
00:43:44,555 --> 00:43:45,656
Ta-da.

627
00:43:52,630 --> 00:43:55,432
That's smart. That's very smart.

628
00:44:00,337 --> 00:44:01,672
Please don't do this to me.

629
00:44:02,840 --> 00:44:05,476
I'm crying even more than when Mom died.

630
00:44:07,411 --> 00:44:08,879
Oh, yes.

631
00:44:08,946 --> 00:44:12,349
A table for two at 9 p.m.
under the name of T&T Mobile.

632
00:44:12,416 --> 00:44:13,751
-Also...
-I said,

633
00:44:13,817 --> 00:44:15,719
I'm not bringing any darn pickles.

634
00:44:16,253 --> 00:44:18,122
Shut up. You better have
only instant rice and pickles

635
00:44:18,188 --> 00:44:19,623
for every meal.

636
00:44:20,224 --> 00:44:21,925
You can't spend all your money eating out

637
00:44:22,159 --> 00:44:23,994
and ask Gal-hee to send more money.

638
00:44:24,395 --> 00:44:25,796
Be quiet, guys.

639
00:44:25,929 --> 00:44:28,265
I've checked everything else on the menu,

640
00:44:28,332 --> 00:44:30,901
but can you tell me what will be served
as an amuse-bouche?

641
00:44:31,468 --> 00:44:33,037
Amuse what?

642
00:44:33,303 --> 00:44:35,039
As you may know,

643
00:44:35,105 --> 00:44:37,107
the chef decides what to serve every day.

644
00:44:37,174 --> 00:44:40,611
I know that, but my boss

645
00:44:40,678 --> 00:44:42,746
has a very bad allergy to peanuts.

646
00:44:43,514 --> 00:44:45,983
Can you at least tell me if any peanuts

647
00:44:46,050 --> 00:44:47,785
will be used in the menu that day?

648
00:44:48,385 --> 00:44:50,654
Okay. Thank you.

649
00:44:51,355 --> 00:44:54,858
Do you even know what amuse-whatever is?

650
00:44:55,159 --> 00:44:56,593
I don't.

651
00:44:57,394 --> 00:45:00,097
And I never will.

652
00:45:00,364 --> 00:45:02,766
Why not? Let's buy some and try.

653
00:45:03,233 --> 00:45:05,469
I'm afraid we can't.

654
00:45:06,470 --> 00:45:07,604
You can't just

655
00:45:07,671 --> 00:45:10,007
order it and try it that easily.

656
00:45:10,641 --> 00:45:12,810
An amuse-bouche is
a part of a French course dinner

657
00:45:12,876 --> 00:45:17,147
where the chef showcases the restaurant's
very best flavors.

658
00:45:17,614 --> 00:45:20,951
In other words, you can only have it

659
00:45:21,051 --> 00:45:24,121
when you have a top-notch course meal

660
00:45:24,855 --> 00:45:26,356
at a top-notch restaurant.

661
00:45:27,791 --> 00:45:29,493
I'm not crying because I'm sad.

662
00:45:30,427 --> 00:45:31,695
It's because of the onion.

663
00:45:33,163 --> 00:45:34,832
Nam-hee,

664
00:45:35,099 --> 00:45:38,402
study abroad and become a person
who can enjoy amuse-bouches.

665
00:45:38,502 --> 00:45:41,672
Don't become a person who has to ask about
an amuse-bouche for someone else.

666
00:45:41,739 --> 00:45:43,340
Okay? Got it?

667
00:45:43,407 --> 00:45:45,342
You're pathetic.

668
00:45:45,843 --> 00:45:48,879
Not everyone is a top student.

669
00:45:50,614 --> 00:45:52,282
Eat it, you silly girl.

670
00:45:52,349 --> 00:45:53,484
What did you say?

671
00:45:53,550 --> 00:45:55,219
Why would you throw that at me?

672
00:45:55,619 --> 00:45:57,554
-I just wanted to give it to you.
-Peel this.

673
00:45:57,621 --> 00:45:59,156
Stop crying.

674
00:46:00,891 --> 00:46:02,526
You're taking the girls to a club tonight?

675
00:46:02,593 --> 00:46:04,128
It must be pretty expensive.

676
00:46:04,461 --> 00:46:05,996
I owe them a lot.

677
00:46:06,497 --> 00:46:08,532
They even threw a goodbye party
for me when I got fired.

678
00:46:10,134 --> 00:46:11,235
But

679
00:46:11,835 --> 00:46:14,505
something happened
to my secretary, Ms. Lee.

680
00:46:14,705 --> 00:46:15,839
So I left.

681
00:46:20,077 --> 00:46:22,112
-Ms. Lee.
-Yes?

682
00:46:22,446 --> 00:46:25,315
What were you doing
when we were having a goodbye party?

683
00:46:26,550 --> 00:46:27,518
What?

684
00:46:27,584 --> 00:46:30,587
Se-yeong said you were coming too,

685
00:46:30,654 --> 00:46:32,055
but you never did.

686
00:46:34,625 --> 00:46:37,027
I was meaning to,

687
00:46:37,094 --> 00:46:38,529
but my mom suddenly got sick,

688
00:46:38,595 --> 00:46:40,831
so I had to go visit her. I'm sorry.

689
00:46:41,331 --> 00:46:43,700
You went to visit your mother?
In Hwangcheon?

690
00:46:43,767 --> 00:46:44,768
Yes.

691
00:46:46,236 --> 00:46:48,539
Mr. Gi said

692
00:46:48,605 --> 00:46:51,608
he left because
something happened to Ms. Lee.

693
00:46:52,009 --> 00:46:55,612
But Ms. Lee was visiting her mother?

694
00:47:02,553 --> 00:47:04,188
You get off work early these days.

695
00:47:06,623 --> 00:47:09,660
Yes, I've tamed my boss completely.

696
00:47:10,027 --> 00:47:11,929
I get off work at 8 p.m.

697
00:47:11,995 --> 00:47:13,197
and take weekends off.

698
00:47:13,430 --> 00:47:15,866
I get an hour of lunch break
every day too.

699
00:47:17,634 --> 00:47:19,036
Are you sure you've tamed him?

700
00:47:19,536 --> 00:47:21,071
Not the other way around?

701
00:47:22,172 --> 00:47:23,207
That's just normal.

702
00:47:23,273 --> 00:47:24,808
Taking weekends off

703
00:47:24,875 --> 00:47:26,443
and getting off work on time.

704
00:47:26,810 --> 00:47:29,813
You're being so happy for getting
what you were supposed to have anyway.

705
00:47:29,980 --> 00:47:31,648
To me, it seems like
you've been tamed by him,

706
00:47:31,715 --> 00:47:33,917
not the other way around.

707
00:47:36,553 --> 00:47:38,288
Your boss has impressive skills.

708
00:47:39,556 --> 00:47:42,226
Pretending to be generous while giving you

709
00:47:42,359 --> 00:47:44,328
only the basic things you deserve anyway.

710
00:47:44,828 --> 00:47:47,564
Turning your legitimate rights
into something to get excited about.

711
00:47:58,775 --> 00:48:01,144
A high-pitched voice.

712
00:48:02,145 --> 00:48:05,148
Fancy clothes. High heels.

713
00:48:06,149 --> 00:48:07,284
With this information,

714
00:48:07,584 --> 00:48:10,120
I'll be able to recognize her
without seeing her face, right?

715
00:48:14,424 --> 00:48:16,326
I already told her the reservation was

716
00:48:16,393 --> 00:48:18,195
under the name of T&T Mobile.

717
00:48:18,795 --> 00:48:21,231
Everything will probably be fine
as long as you find the right table.

718
00:48:25,035 --> 00:48:26,536
"Probably"?

719
00:48:28,839 --> 00:48:31,541
Do you know who Veronica Park is?

720
00:48:31,909 --> 00:48:34,778
She has the whole movie world
under her thumb.

721
00:48:35,078 --> 00:48:36,914
Even if I'll never see her again,

722
00:48:37,080 --> 00:48:38,982
I can't afford to get
on the wrong side of her.

723
00:48:39,683 --> 00:48:40,918
What do you know?

724
00:48:44,321 --> 00:48:47,724
So there is someone you're scared of.

725
00:48:50,894 --> 00:48:55,132
I thought you treated everyone
in the world the way you treat me.

726
00:48:55,799 --> 00:48:56,800
What?

727
00:48:59,336 --> 00:49:00,470
Nothing.

728
00:49:03,774 --> 00:49:06,510
You'd better leave early.

729
00:49:06,877 --> 00:49:09,179
There's a protest going on at Gwanghwamun.

730
00:49:09,413 --> 00:49:11,181
The traffic is really bad.

731
00:49:13,183 --> 00:49:14,284
See you.

732
00:49:18,322 --> 00:49:19,523
What's with her?

733
00:49:25,996 --> 00:49:28,265
-No way.
-It's true.

734
00:49:28,498 --> 00:49:30,267
Sorry I'm late, guys.

735
00:49:31,535 --> 00:49:32,703
-Hey!
-Hey!

736
00:49:33,270 --> 00:49:35,572
Gosh. What?

737
00:49:36,206 --> 00:49:38,742
Are you going to dig up sweet potatoes
or pick mugworts?

738
00:49:39,009 --> 00:49:40,811
You want to go to a club
looking like this?

739
00:49:41,745 --> 00:49:43,947
I'm wearing contacts
instead of my glasses.

740
00:49:46,416 --> 00:49:50,153
You said we'd have a blast.
But in that rag?

741
00:49:50,487 --> 00:49:52,956
What you should've taken off is
that darn cardigan, not your glasses!

742
00:49:53,690 --> 00:49:56,460
Is it that bad?

743
00:49:56,793 --> 00:49:57,694
-I'm dizzy.
-Se-yeong.

744
00:49:57,761 --> 00:50:00,564
There are some clothes in the paper bag.
Change her into whatever.

745
00:50:01,531 --> 00:50:03,033
Gosh.

746
00:50:03,400 --> 00:50:05,635
Do I even have to dress her now?

747
00:50:06,603 --> 00:50:09,039
Take that cardigan off right now.
It kills my imagination.

748
00:50:09,106 --> 00:50:10,774
-Throw it away.
-Please.

749
00:50:22,853 --> 00:50:24,421
What should we do?

750
00:50:25,155 --> 00:50:26,990
You might be a little late.

751
00:50:31,795 --> 00:50:33,764
-It's that place, right?
-Yes.

752
00:50:34,765 --> 00:50:36,266
I'll get off here.

753
00:50:36,366 --> 00:50:37,634
It'll be faster if I run.

754
00:50:55,185 --> 00:50:58,255
-Exactly.
-I told you.

755
00:51:03,460 --> 00:51:04,761
Take it easy.

756
00:51:05,062 --> 00:51:06,196
You can't stop me.

757
00:51:06,263 --> 00:51:08,131
This isn't about you anymore.

758
00:51:08,298 --> 00:51:10,600
This is a battle
between me and your eyebrows.

759
00:51:11,201 --> 00:51:14,471
How funny. This is giving me
a strange sense of accomplishment.

760
00:51:14,971 --> 00:51:18,608
Do I even have to put earrings on her now?

761
00:51:22,913 --> 00:51:24,481
I wonder if he's arrived.

762
00:51:24,748 --> 00:51:26,183
The traffic is supposed to be really bad.

763
00:51:42,766 --> 00:51:47,537
MS. JEONG

764
00:51:49,539 --> 00:51:51,374
-Why isn't he picking up?
-The person you dialed...

765
00:51:56,746 --> 00:51:59,816
I'm calling from T&T Mobile.
Has Ms. Park left?

766
00:52:00,183 --> 00:52:01,885
I'm sure she's already arrived.

767
00:52:02,219 --> 00:52:03,987
Her last appointment was in Samseong-dong,

768
00:52:04,054 --> 00:52:06,256
so he went straight to the Princess Hotel.

769
00:52:06,857 --> 00:52:07,891
Pardon?

770
00:52:08,091 --> 00:52:09,159
-Hey!
-Hey!

771
00:52:09,359 --> 00:52:11,161
Why the Princess Hotel?

772
00:52:11,228 --> 00:52:14,264
I clearly said the Kingdom Hotel!

773
00:52:14,331 --> 00:52:17,100
Right? That's what I heard too.

774
00:52:17,167 --> 00:52:19,236
But Ms. Park insisted
it was the Princess Hotel.

775
00:52:19,503 --> 00:52:20,804
Darn it.

776
00:52:23,707 --> 00:52:24,975
-Gal-hee!
-Gal-hee!

777
00:52:37,053 --> 00:52:40,557
Nice to meet you. I'm Veronica Park.

778
00:52:44,761 --> 00:52:45,996
Nice to meet you.

779
00:52:46,062 --> 00:52:48,031
I'm Gi Dae-ju of T&T Mobile.

780
00:52:48,498 --> 00:52:49,599
Gi Dae-ju?

781
00:52:58,241 --> 00:52:59,442
What happened?

782
00:53:00,043 --> 00:53:02,012
That's what I want to ask you.

783
00:53:02,078 --> 00:53:03,947
Why are you at the Princess Hotel?
I clearly said

784
00:53:04,014 --> 00:53:06,016
the Kingdom Hotel.

785
00:53:11,421 --> 00:53:14,024
T&T Mobile will contact you.

786
00:53:15,058 --> 00:53:19,563
Try to behave this time,

787
00:53:20,163 --> 00:53:21,364
okay?

788
00:53:24,401 --> 00:53:26,770
I never say no to guys.

789
00:53:27,037 --> 00:53:29,172
Do Min-ik.

790
00:53:37,948 --> 00:53:41,051
Ms. Park, I'm Sim Hae-yong of T&T Mobile.

791
00:53:41,685 --> 00:53:43,653
I've been waiting.

792
00:53:43,787 --> 00:53:44,854
Really?

793
00:53:46,590 --> 00:53:50,026
I'd like to set you up with a guy
I'm very fond of.

794
00:53:55,532 --> 00:53:58,668
How about the Princess Hotel
at 9 p.m. on the 13th?

795
00:53:58,969 --> 00:54:01,838
Okay. I'll be on time.

796
00:54:05,675 --> 00:54:09,079
So who's this amazing boss of yours?

797
00:54:09,479 --> 00:54:12,882
I work for Mr. Do Min-ik of T&T Mobile.

798
00:54:13,950 --> 00:54:18,288
Now I know what happened.

799
00:54:18,555 --> 00:54:20,257
There must have been a mistake.

800
00:54:20,323 --> 00:54:21,925
Let me find Mr. Do

801
00:54:21,992 --> 00:54:24,094
and tell him you'll be a bit late.

802
00:54:24,160 --> 00:54:25,195
No.

803
00:54:31,735 --> 00:54:35,071
Every mistake can be turned into a tango.

804
00:54:35,272 --> 00:54:37,474
Have I told you
that's my favorite movie quote?

805
00:54:38,174 --> 00:54:40,777
What about it though?

806
00:54:41,444 --> 00:54:44,347
I thought it suited
the situation perfectly.

807
00:54:44,714 --> 00:54:46,850
I might have gotten all tangled up,

808
00:54:47,450 --> 00:54:51,254
but I have a feeling
this dance will be a lot of fun.

809
00:54:52,122 --> 00:54:55,458
You find your way
out of this tangle now. See you.

810
00:54:58,295 --> 00:55:00,263
Ms. Park! Hello?

811
00:55:08,405 --> 00:55:11,241
Gosh, why did these two
have to get tangled up now?

812
00:55:13,376 --> 00:55:16,012
I nagged him so much

813
00:55:16,780 --> 00:55:18,315
to show up prepared.

814
00:55:19,649 --> 00:55:21,217
I'll go there

815
00:55:21,818 --> 00:55:23,520
and tell him the truth.

816
00:55:33,563 --> 00:55:34,831
Excuse me.

817
00:55:34,898 --> 00:55:36,633
If you have to wait a bit longer,

818
00:55:36,700 --> 00:55:39,436
would you like an amuse-bouche
and some bread served first?

819
00:55:41,604 --> 00:55:43,673
-Yes, please.
-Sure.

820
00:55:49,412 --> 00:55:50,880
I'm so sorry, guys.

821
00:55:51,014 --> 00:55:53,049
The old man just left.

822
00:55:53,283 --> 00:55:55,385
I can get there in 10 minutes by taxi.

823
00:55:55,618 --> 00:55:56,953
Stay right there, all of you.

824
00:55:57,921 --> 00:56:01,157
I have so much information
to get out of Gal-hee tonight.

825
00:56:02,792 --> 00:56:03,960
Jeong-su?

826
00:56:09,399 --> 00:56:10,500
Jeong-su.

827
00:56:11,368 --> 00:56:12,769
What are you doing here?

828
00:56:14,137 --> 00:56:16,239
You can't be here!

829
00:57:00,550 --> 00:57:01,985
I've been waiting for you.

830
00:57:04,320 --> 00:57:05,388
Pardon?

831
00:57:12,629 --> 00:57:16,566
Sometimes, one minute
can change everything.

832
00:57:37,086 --> 00:57:40,590
That moment, I felt a sudden urge
to sit in the chair

833
00:57:40,790 --> 00:57:42,625
he pulled out for me.

834
00:57:44,994 --> 00:57:46,830
Here's today's amuse-bouche.

835
00:57:54,571 --> 00:57:56,739
I also wanted to taste an amuse-bouche

836
00:57:57,640 --> 00:58:00,210
I thought I'd never get to taste
in my life.

837
00:58:00,376 --> 00:58:01,544
And...

838
00:58:09,486 --> 00:58:10,920
I wanted to know

839
00:58:12,489 --> 00:58:16,526
how this man would treat a woman

840
00:58:17,060 --> 00:58:19,095
who wasn't me.

841
00:58:23,333 --> 00:58:24,300
Right.

842
00:58:25,435 --> 00:58:28,571
I'm sorry I forgot to introduce myself.

843
00:58:30,740 --> 00:58:32,041
Nice to meet you.

844
00:58:36,012 --> 00:58:37,347
I'm Do Min-ik.

845
00:58:42,085 --> 00:58:43,386
Thank you for everything.

846
00:58:48,424 --> 00:58:49,592
That was

847
00:58:50,727 --> 00:58:53,730
the minute that changed my life.

848
00:59:01,004 --> 00:59:01,971
Nice to meet you.

849
00:59:02,038 --> 00:59:04,440
I'm Veronica Park.

850
00:59:27,463 --> 00:59:29,999
Why are you staring at me like that?

851
00:59:30,500 --> 00:59:33,603
It's just that you're quite different
from what I expected.

852
00:59:34,537 --> 00:59:36,406
Give me Veronica Park's phone number.

853
00:59:36,472 --> 00:59:38,841
So give me that guy's phone number.

854
00:59:42,045 --> 00:59:43,379
I found it, Boss.

855
00:59:43,580 --> 00:59:46,149
Who are you? No way. Is it you?

856
00:59:46,215 --> 00:59:47,150
No!

857
00:59:48,785 --> 00:59:50,787
Subtitle translation by Min-jin Kim

